OL,3,CIFS accuses Labour and Tories of
OL,4,C'conspiracy of silence' over manifestos
OL,6,FIt said both parties had presented the
OL,7,Fpublic with a choice of either "higher
OL,8,Ftaxes or worse public services",
OL,9,Fadding that voters have been left
OL,10,Fguessing over policy on tax and
OL,11,Fspending, and on the future size and
OL,12,Fshape of the state.
OL,14,FThe IFS released its analysis on
OL,15,FMonday, with its director, Paul
OL,16,FJohnson, saying the "raw facts" of the
OL,17,Feconomy - including that UK debt is at
OL,18,Fits highest level for 60 years - are
OL,19,Fbeing "largely ignored by the two main
OL,20,Fparties in their manifestos".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
