OL,3,CIFS accuses Labour and Tories of
OL,4,C'conspiracy of silence' over manifestos
OL,6,FLabour has pledged not to raise income
OL,7,Ftax, VAT or national insurance, with
OL,8,Fthe Tories also ruling out increases
OL,9,Ffor the former two as well as
OL,10,Fcommitting to a third 2p reduction as
OL,11,Fpart of a drive to eliminate national
OL,12,Finsurance altogether.
OL,14,FBut the IFS said the decisions have
OL,15,Fenacted "something of a tax lock arms
OL,16,Frace", adding both parties have "tied
OL,17,Ftheir hands on income tax, NICs, VAT
OL,18,Fand corporation tax".
