OL,3,CIFS accuses Labour and Tories of
OL,4,C'conspiracy of silence' over manifestos
OL,6,FPromises from both parties to improve
OL,7,Fthe NHS were labelled as "unfunded
OL,8,Fcommitments", which imply that cuts to
OL,9,Fhospital waiting lists and plans to
OL,10,Fbuild more hospitals, among other
OL,11,Fpledges, can be "delivered for free".
OL,13,F"It can't," The IFS' report read. "You
OL,14,Fcan't pledge to end all waits of more
OL,15,Fthan 18 weeks, allocate no money to
OL,16,Fthat pledge, and then claim to have a
OL,17,Ffully costed manifesto.
